### Feature A: Subject-wise Attendance Tracking

#### How It Works

```
Student logs in â†’ Dashboard loads â†’ API call to /api/attendance/summary/:studentId
                                           â†“
                                  Backend calculates per subject:
                                  - Present count
                                  - Total lectures conducted
                                  - Percentage
                                  - Status color
                                           â†“
                                  Returns JSON array to Angular
                                           â†“
                                  Angular renders attendance cards
```

#### Attendance Card Component

```typescript
// Angular Component Data Structure
interface AttendanceCard {
  subjectId: string;
  subjectName: string;
  subjectCode: string;
  present: number;        // e.g., 39
  total: number;          // e.g., 50
  percentage: number;     // e.g., 78
  status: 'safe' | 'warning' | 'danger';
  canMiss: number;        // lectures student can still miss
}
```

#### Percentage Calculation Logic

```javascript
// Backend calculation (Node.js)
function calculateAttendance(studentId, subjectId) {
  // Count present lectures from Attendance collection
  const presentCount = await Attendance.countDocuments({
    studentId,
    subjectId,
    status: 'present'
  });

  // Get total lectures conducted
  const subject = await Subject.findById(subjectId);
  const totalConducted = subject.lecturesConducted;

  // Calculate percentage
  const percentage = totalConducted > 0 
    ? Math.round((presentCount / totalConducted) * 100) 
    : 100;

  return { present: presentCount, total: totalConducted, percentage };
}
```

